<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 24th January 2025</p>

    <h2>Welcome to FridayFilmClub!</h2>
    <p>
        Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting the personal information you share with us. 
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our platform to chat with 
        others, rate films, and enjoy our services.
    </p>

    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
    <h4>1.1 Personal Information</h4>
    <p>When you sign up for <strong>FridayFilmClub</strong>, we may collect:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Your name or username.</li>
        <li>Email address.</li>
        <li>Profile picture (if uploaded).</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>1.2 Non-Personal Information</h4>
    <p>We automatically collect certain data when you use our platform, such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Browser type and operating system.</li>
        <li>IP address.</li>
        <li>Date and time of access.</li>
        <li>Pages visited and interaction data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>1.3 User-Generated Content</h4>
    <p>
        When you use features like chatting, posting reviews, or rating films, the content you share 
        (e.g., comments, ratings, messages) may also be collected.
    </p>

    <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
    <p>We use your information to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and improve the website's features and services.</li>
        <li>Facilitate chatting and interaction between users.</li>
        <li>Personalize your experience (e.g., recommending films based on your ratings).</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about updates, promotions, or account-related issues.</li>
        <li>Ensure the safety and integrity of our platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. How We Share Your Information</h3>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following cases:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> To operate and maintain the website (e.g., hosting, analytics).</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> If required by law or in response to valid legal requests.</li>
        <li><strong>Protecting Our Platform:</strong> To detect and prevent fraud, security threats, or abuse.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
    <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience, analyze site usage, and remember your preferences. 
        You can manage or disable cookies through your browser settings, but doing so may limit some functionalities of the site.
    </p>

    <h3>5. Data Security</h3>
    <p>
        We take data protection seriously and implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal information. 
        However, no online platform is entirely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security. Please use the platform responsibly 
        and avoid sharing sensitive information.
    </p>

    <h3>6. Your Rights</h3>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access and review the personal information we hold about you.</li>
        <li>Request corrections to inaccurate information.</li>
        <li>Delete your account and associated data.</li>
        <li>Opt-out of receiving promotional emails.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <strong>[Insert Contact Email]</strong>.</p>

    <h3>7. Third-Party Links</h3>
    <p>
        Our website may include links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or 
        content of these websites. Please review their privacy policies before providing any information.
    </p>

    <h3>8. Children’s Privacy</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>FridayFilmClub</strong> is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect 
        personal information from children. If we become aware that a child has provided us with personal information, 
        we will delete it promptly.
    </p>

    <h3>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the 
        "Effective Date" at the top will be updated. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed.
    </p>

